CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 16, 1961, pg. 7, reads: "Encourages NAACP Pickets - James McCoy, left, and Matthew Moore, two members of the local NAACP board, listed attentively as a shopper offers strong encouragement in theihr [sic] picketing of Fifth Ave. shoe stores which do not employ Negroes as sales clerks. The current drive has resulted in success at several Pittsburgh stores. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: NAACP protesters James "Jim" McCoy and Matthew Moore, in front of Beck Shoe Store with signs inscribed "Help Mr. K. in Washington, Hurt Mr. K in Moscow," Fifth Avenue, Downtown
